hweppes in  the snapple turnaround was featured as a harvard business school case study in  peltz may and ed garden founded trian fund management lp as an activist investing firm trian has invested in such companies as heinz cadbury kraft foods ingersoll rand wendy’s dupont mondelēz pepsico state street corporation  and family dollar in  trian was involved in a proxy contest with heinz to get five independent directors on the board of heinz trian succeeded in getting two members on the board including peltz in  trian bought a  share of cadburyschweppes cadbury schweppes americas beverages was later spun off from the cadbury schweppes confectionery group in  trian also bought  billion in shares of kraft foods roughly a  of the total equity of the food maker in april  it was announced that triarc cos would merge with burger chain wendys the merger was completed on september   the new company was named wendys arbys group and traded on the new york stock exchange under the symbol wen on july   wendys arbys sold arbys to roark capital group and changed its name to the wendys company according to cnbc on february   trian offered to buy family dollar for – per share in february  trian announced it had accumulated an  stake in the family dollar company and indicated a willingness to participate in a take private lbo for the company with a total value of about  to  billion this overture was rejected by the company management and board of directors in september  ed garden trian’s chief investment officer joined the family dollar board peltz was appointed to the ingersollrand board of directors in  in august  it was reported that trian held an approximate  billion stake in dupont in january  as one of the company’s largest shareholders with a current beneficial ownership of more than  million shares peltz was appointed to the board of directors of global snacking company mondelēz international nasdaq mdlz in february  as a beneficial owner of approximately  billion of pepsico inc nyse pep common shares trian publicly released a letter to pepsico’s board of directors and a white paper detailing why separating global snacks and beverages into two independent public companies would be the right longterm decision for the business and would create substantial value for shareholders trian said it would immediately begin to engage fellow shareholders in a public dialogue with the goal of creating a groundswell of support for a separation of snacks and beverages in february  forbes listed peltz as one of the  highestearning hedge fund managers in  with total earnings of  million ranked th in may  trian was unsuccessful in a bitter proxy contest to appoint four of its nominees to the board of dupont five months later the ceo of dupont ellen kullman resigned at the time dupont acknowledged lower than expected earnings and the need to accelerate a costcutting plan in october  trian bought a  billion stake in general electric personal lifeedit peltzs children will and nicola at the  toronto international film festival peltz has been married three times his third wife is claudia heffner a former fashion model with whom he has eight children he has two children from his prior marriages among peltzs children are actors nicola peltz and will peltz his son brad peltz was a professional ice hockey player who played in the echl during the – echl season peltz resides in bedford new york he also owns montsorrel which is his house in palm beach florida previously owned by anita young the sister of georgia okeeffe he has recently begun a refurbishment and expansion project for the property wealth and philanthropyedit according to forbes magazine he has a net worth of  billion as of february  this makes him the nd richest person in the us in  peltz was among  entities that contributed the maximum of  to the second inauguration of president george w bush he is also a heavy contributor to jewish causes awards and recognitionedit he was recognized by the national association of corporate directors nacd in   and  as among the most influential people in global corporate governance referencesedit  a b nelson peltzs house virtualglobetrottingcom retrieved february     a b forbes the worlds billionaires nelson peltz february   a b c duane d stanford january   mondelez names peltz director as investor seen pushing cuts bloomberg   a b anupreeta das and sharon terlep august   activist peltz wins board seat at ingersoll the wall street journal   a b biography nelson peltz wendys retrieved april     a b shawn tully march   the reinvention of nelson peltz cnnmoneycom   company overview of trian fund management lp bloomberg businessweek retrieved april     fortune  fortune magazine retrieved april     a b c d jewish virtual library nelson peltz by nancy a ruhling retrieved january    maurice peltz  built family food business into a major marketer the new york times    paid notice deaths peltz claire the new york times    wall street frats business insider retrieved  february    a b katherine burton and sree vidya bhaktavatsalam september   peltz gets  billion as activist strategy impresses bloomberg news   palm beach daily news matisse  the younger coming by cholly knickerbocker january    frozen food heiress gladys peltz poppa owns snow crop  a b business people sale wont end career of peltz foods owner the new york times august     entrepreneurs turn tin into gold sale of can firm may bring owners  million sun sentinel november     pechiney sa launches a tender offer for triangle industries inc from trian group lp thomson reuters january   retrieved july     a b john deighton february   how a juicy brand came back to life harvard business school   miles weiss february   peltz helped spur heinz turnaround setting stage for bid bloomberg   antoine gara january   pepsi challenge wheres the pact between mondelez and trian thestreetcom   ingersollrand to spin off security business sources reuters december     michelle celarier august   peltz dines on wendy’s stake new york post   a b jack kaskey and beth jinks august   peltz’s trian said to meet dupont’s ceo boosts stake bloomberg   let my fritos go the economist march     sharon terlep january   state street stake pared by activist investor the wall street journal   maureen farrell january   family dollar next retailer up for sale the wall street journal   dan burrows august   heinz proxy fight comes down to the wire marketwatchcom   shawn tully and matthew boyle june   peltz has his slice of kraft  now what cnnmoneycom   josh fineman and zachary mider april   peltzs triarc to buy wendys combine it with arbys bloomberg   triarc and wendys complete merger transaction business wire september     wendy’sarbys group completes sale of arbys to roark capital group wendys july     chris burritt march   family dollar rejects buyout offer from peltzs trian adopts poison pill bloomberg   family dollar appoints edward garden of trian partners to board of directors bloomberg september     das anupreeta terlep sharon august   activist peltz wins board seat at ingersoll the wall street journal p b   activist investor nelson peltz joins mondelez board chicagotribune retrieved  february    matt egan january   proxy war averted mondelez adds activist nelson peltz to board fox business network   duane d stanford february   peltz renews pepsico breakup proposal in rebuke of ceo nooyi bloomberg   siddharth cavale february   nelson peltz revives campaign to split up pepsico reuters   vardi nathan feb   the  highestearning hedge fund managers and traders forbes   bunge jacob may   dupont defeats peltz trian in board fight  wsj wsjcom retrieved may     merced michael j de la  dupont chief executive ellen kullman to retire the new york times issn  retrieved    nelson peltzs trian takes  billion stake in general electric reuters  october    tully shawn march   cnn money the reinvention of nelson peltz  baker tom  airbender ideal sweet but strong daily yomiuri online retrie